
Overview of noun skirt

The noun skirt has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (4) skirt -- (cloth covering that forms the part of a garment below the waist)
2. (2) skirt -- (a garment hanging from the waist; worn mainly by girls and women)
3. annulus, skirt -- ((Fungi) a remnant of the partial veil that in mature mushrooms surrounds the stem like a collar)
4. dame, doll, wench, skirt, chick, bird -- (informal terms for a (young) woman)

Overview of verb skirt

